name: Aegis of Honor
text: {1}: The next time an instant or sorcery spell would deal damage to you this turn, that spell deals that damage to its controller instead.

name: Ancestral Tribute
text: You gain 2 life for each card in your graveyard.\nFlashback {9}{W}{W}{W} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Angelic Wall
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\nFlying
flavor: "The Ancestor protects us in ways we can't begin to comprehend."\n—Mystic elder

name: Animal Boneyard
text: Enchant land\nEnchanted land has "{T}, Sacrifice a creature: You gain life equal to the sacrificed creature's toughness."
flavor: "The animal spirits are the Ancestor's grandchildren. Remember them."\n—Mystic elder

name: Auramancer
text: When Auramancer enters the battlefield, you may return target enchantment card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: Beauty stirs the memory like a sweet perfume excites the air.

name: Aven Archer
text: Flying\n{2}{W}, {T}: Aven Archer deals 2 damage to target attacking or blocking creature.
flavor: Aimed by the eyes of eagles, their arrows never miss the mark.

name: Aven Cloudchaser
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nWhen Aven Cloudchaser enters the battlefield, destroy target enchantment.
flavor: "At the Reapportionment, Eagle begged to be human. The Ancestor granted half that prayer."\n—Nomad myth

name: Aven Flock
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\n{W}: Aven Flock gets +0/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: Just as each added feather steadies the wing, so does the flock grow stronger with each new member.

name: Aven Shrine
text: Whenever a player casts a spell, that player gains X life, where X is the number of cards in all graveyards with the same name as that spell.

name: Balancing Act
text: Each player chooses a number of permanents he or she controls equal to the number of permanents controlled by the player who controls the fewest, then sacrifices the rest. Each player discards cards the same way.

name: Beloved Chaplain
text: Protection from creatures
flavor: Nomad and Nantuko, eagle and elephant; all the birds and beasts are charmed by his quiet dignity.

name: Blessed Orator
text: Other creatures you control get +0/+1.
flavor: His quiet words fade into the night's chill, yet they burn into his listeners' minds with all the power of a thousand suns.

name: Cantivore
text: Vigilance\nCantivore's power and toughness are each equal to the number of enchantment cards in all graveyards.

name: Cease-Fire
text: Target player can't cast creature spells this turn.\nDraw a card.
flavor: When the crimson fades from the magical embers, a final wisp of smoke will rise. Soon after, hostilities will begin anew.

name: Confessor
text: Whenever a player discards a card, you may gain 1 life.
flavor: "There will be gains for our losses. There will be rights for our wrongs."

name: Dedicated Martyr
text: {W}, Sacrifice Dedicated Martyr: You gain 3 life.
flavor: "If he's so willing to suffer for his cause, then by all means, let us oblige him."\n—Cabal Patriarch

name: Delaying Shield
text: If damage would be dealt to you, put that many delay counters on Delaying Shield instead.\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, remove all delay counters from Delaying Shield. For each delay counter removed this way, you lose 1 life unless you pay {1}{W}.

name: Devoted Caretaker
text: {W}, {T}: Target permanent you control gains protection from instant spells and from sorcery spells until end of turn.
flavor: Her eyes blaze with the strength of twenty shields. Every glance is a salvation.

name: Divine Sacrament
text: White creatures get +1/+1.\nThreshold — White creatures get an additional +1/+1 as long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard.
flavor: Their whispered prayers rally the nomads better than any war cry could.

name: Dogged Hunter
text: {T}: Destroy target creature token.
flavor: The relationship between hunter and hunted knows nothing of alliances.

name: Earnest Fellowship
text: Each creature has protection from its colors.
flavor: "The world has enough strife as it is. Where would we be if we turned against each other?"\n—Pianna, nomad captain

name: Embolden
text: Prevent the next 4 damage that would be dealt this turn to any number of target creatures and/or players, divided as you choose.\nFlashback {1}{W} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Gallantry
text: Target blocking creature gets +4/+4 until end of turn.\nDraw a card.
flavor: The courageous accomplish more in a single moment than the cowardly do in a lifetime.

name: Graceful Antelope
text: Plainswalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Plains.)\nWhenever Graceful Antelope deals combat damage to a player, you may have target land become a Plains until Graceful Antelope leaves the battlefield.

name: Hallowed Healer
text: {T}: Prevent the next 2 damage that would be dealt to target creature or player this turn.\nThreshold — {T}: Prevent the next 4 damage that would be dealt to target creature or player this turn. Activate this ability only if seven or more cards are in your graveyard.

name: Karmic Justice
text: Whenever a spell or ability an opponent controls destroys a noncreature permanent you control, you may destroy target permanent that opponent controls.

name: Kirtar's Desire
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature can't attack.\nThreshold — Enchanted creature can't block as long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard.

name: Kirtar's Wrath
text: Destroy all creatures. They can't be regenerated.\nThreshold — If seven or more cards are in your graveyard, instead destroy all creatures, then put two 1/1 white Spirit creature tokens with flying onto the battlefield. Creatures destroyed this way can't be regenerated.

name: Lieutenant Kirtar
text: Flying\n{1}{W}, Sacrifice Lieutenant Kirtar: Exile target attacking creature.
flavor: "His strengths are pride, devotion, and ambition. His weaknesses are the same."\n—Pianna, nomad captain

name: Life Burst
text: Target player gains 4 life, then gains 4 life for each card named Life Burst in each graveyard.
flavor: As uplifting as a mystic's dreams.

name: Luminous Guardian
text: {W}: Luminous Guardian gets +0/+1 until end of turn.\n{2}: Luminous Guardian can block an additional creature this turn.
flavor: "There is no victory without virtue."

name: Master Apothecary
text: Tap an untapped Cleric you control: Prevent the next 2 damage that would be dealt to target creature or player this turn.
flavor: It takes a remarkable cleric to turn a group of healers into a hospital.

name: Mystic Crusader
text: Protection from black and from red\nThreshold — As long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard, Mystic Crusader gets +1/+1 and has flying.

name: Mystic Penitent
text: Vigilance\nThreshold — As long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard, Mystic Penitent gets +1/+1 and has flying.

name: Mystic Visionary
text: Threshold — Mystic Visionary has flying as long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard.
flavor: "The aven are heralds of divinity. The greatest glory is to join them in the sky."

name: Mystic Zealot
text: Threshold — As long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard, Mystic Zealot gets +1/+1 and has flying.
flavor: Nomad youths aspire to one of two roles in the tribe: priest or warrior. Their secret dream is to become both.

name: Nomad Decoy
text: {W}, {T}: Tap target creature.\nThreshold — {W}{W}, {T}: Tap two target creatures. Activate this ability only if seven or more cards are in your graveyard.
flavor: If you can take something from a nomad, it's probably bait.

name: Patrol Hound
text: Discard a card: Patrol Hound gains first strike until end of turn.
flavor: To the camp, it was a fierce and loyal protector. To the sentry's youngest daughter, it would always be her "Wuv Muffin."

name: Pianna, Nomad Captain
text: Whenever Pianna, Nomad Captain attacks, attacking creatures get +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: Some find inspiration in their swords. Others find it in their leaders.

name: Pilgrim of Justice
text: Protection from red\n{W}, Sacrifice Pilgrim of Justice: The next time a red source of your choice would deal damage this turn, prevent that damage.
flavor: "I would die a thousand deaths before I let you harm another."

name: Pilgrim of Virtue
text: Protection from black\n{W}, Sacrifice Pilgrim of Virtue: The next time a black source of your choice would deal damage this turn, prevent that damage.
flavor: "A life is measured by the lives it saves."

name: Ray of Distortion
text: Destroy target artifact or enchantment.\nFlashback {4}{W}{W} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Resilient Wanderer
text: First strike\nDiscard a card: Resilient Wanderer gains protection from the color of your choice until end of turn.
flavor: Nomads understand many cultures and therefore travel without fear.

name: Sacred Rites
text: Discard any number of cards. Creatures you control get +0/+1 until end of turn for each card discarded this way.

name: Second Thoughts
text: Exile target attacking creature.\nDraw a card.
flavor: It suddenly dawned on Jorin that farming was quite a noble profession.

name: Shelter
text: Target creature you control gains protection from the color of your choice until end of turn.\nDraw a card.
flavor: Good strategists seize opportunities. Great strategists make their own.

name: Soulcatcher
text: Flying\nWhenever a creature with flying dies, put a +1/+1 counter on Soulcatcher.
flavor: "Holy couriers guide aven spirits up to the home of the Ancestor."\n—Mystic elder

name: Sphere of Duty
text: If a green source would deal damage to you, prevent 2 of that damage.
flavor: Duty subdues instinct.

name: Sphere of Grace
text: If a black source would deal damage to you, prevent 2 of that damage.
flavor: Grace repels darkness.

name: Sphere of Law
text: If a red source would deal damage to you, prevent 2 of that damage.
flavor: Law smothers anarchy.

name: Sphere of Reason
text: If a blue source would deal damage to you, prevent 2 of that damage.
flavor: Reason exposes deception.

name: Sphere of Truth
text: If a white source would deal damage to you, prevent 2 of that damage.
flavor: Truth tempers fanaticism.

name: Spiritualize
text: Until end of turn, whenever target creature deals damage, you gain that much life.\nDraw a card.
flavor: "There is purity in all things. Even hatred."\n—Lieutenant Kirtar

name: Tattoo Ward
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +1/+1 and has protection from enchantments. This effect doesn't remove Tattoo Ward.\nSacrifice Tattoo Ward: Destroy target enchantment.

name: Testament of Faith
text: {X}: Testament of Faith becomes an X/X Wall creature with defender in addition to its other types until end of turn.
flavor: "Belief in the Ancestor is admirable, but our enemies often demand something more . . . tangible."\n—Pianna, nomad captain

name: Tireless Tribe
text: Discard a card: Tireless Tribe gets +0/+4 until end of turn.
flavor: "We've survived starvation, dwarf attacks, and heatstroke. Why should a little sandstorm bother us?"

name: Wayward Angel
text: Flying, vigilance\nThreshold — As long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard, Wayward Angel gets +3/+3, is black, has trample, and has "At the beginning of your upkeep, sacrifice a creature."

name: Aboshan, Cephalid Emperor
text: Tap an untapped Cephalid you control: Tap target permanent.\n{U}{U}{U}: Tap all creatures without flying.
flavor: "No one can fight the tide forever."

name: Aboshan's Desire
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature has flying.\nThreshold — Enchanted creature has shroud as long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard. (It can't be the target of spells or abilities.)

name: Æther Burst
text: Return up to X target creatures to their owners' hands, where X is one plus the number of cards named Æther Burst in all graveyards as you cast Æther Burst.
flavor: As fleeting as a cephalid's promise.

name: Amugaba
text: Flying\n{2}{U}, Discard a card: Return Amugaba to its owner's hand.
flavor: The aven claim it feeds on thunder and rainbows.

name: Aura Graft
text: Gain control of target Aura that's attached to a permanent. Attach it to another permanent it can enchant.
flavor: "It's not really stealing. It's more like extended borrowing."

name: Aven Fisher
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nWhen Aven Fisher dies, you may draw a card.
flavor: The same spears that catch their food today will defend their homes tomorrow.

name: Aven Smokeweaver
text: Flying, protection from red
flavor: In a world still pained from burns, some are born already scarred.

name: Aven Windreader
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\n{1}{U}: Target player reveals the top card of his or her library.
flavor: "The tiniest ripple tells a story ten fathoms deep."

name: Balshan Beguiler
text: Whenever Balshan Beguiler deals combat damage to a player, that player reveals the top two cards of his or her library. You choose one of those cards and put it into his or her graveyard.

name: Balshan Griffin
text: Flying\n{1}{U}, Discard a card: Return Balshan Griffin to its owner's hand.
flavor: It helps to have an extra direction in which to run.

name: Bamboozle
text: Target player reveals the top four cards of his or her library. You choose two of those cards and put them into his or her graveyard. Put the rest on top of his or her library in any order.

name: Battle of Wits
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, if you have 200 or more cards in your library, you win the game.
flavor: The wizard who reads a thousand books is powerful. The wizard who memorizes a thousand books is insane.

name: Careful Study
text: Draw two cards, then discard two cards.
flavor: Books are like crops—they must be thinned for best yield.

name: Cephalid Broker
text: {T}: Target player draws two cards, then discards two cards.
flavor: Cephalids value the free exchange of ideas—except for the "free" part.

name: Cephalid Looter
text: {T}: Target player draws a card, then discards a card.
flavor: "Amazing, isn't it, what humans will throw away when they're drowning?"

name: Cephalid Retainer
text: {U}{U}: Tap target creature without flying.
flavor: Cephalids whisper flattery in your ear, put jewels in your hand, spin dreams in your head, and stick knives in your back.

name: Cephalid Scout
text: Flying\n{2}{U}, Sacrifice a land: Draw a card.
flavor: The more they survey the dreadful dry expanses, the more the cephalids thirst to tame them.

name: Cephalid Shrine
text: Whenever a player casts a spell, counter that spell unless that player pays {X}, where X is the number of cards in all graveyards with the same name as the spell.

name: Chamber of Manipulation
text: Enchant land\nEnchanted land has "{T}, Discard a card: Gain control of target creature until end of turn."
flavor: Politics is just a subtle form of mind control—and cephalids are master politicians.

name: Cognivore
text: Flying\nCognivore's power and toughness are each equal to the number of instant cards in all graveyards.

name: Concentrate
text: Draw three cards.
flavor: "The treasure in my mind is greater than any worldly glory."

name: Cultural Exchange
text: Choose any number of creatures target player controls. Choose the same number of creatures another target player controls. Those players exchange control of those creatures. (This effect lasts indefinitely.)

name: Deluge
text: Tap all creatures without flying.
flavor: "From the sea came all life, and to the sea it will return. The sooner the better."\n—Emperor Aboshan

name: Dematerialize
text: Return target permanent to its owner's hand.\nFlashback {5}{U}{U} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Divert
text: Change the target of target spell with a single target unless that spell's controller pays {2}.
flavor: "What's the fun of being a wizard if you can't mess with people's heads?"

name: Dreamwinder
text: Dreamwinder can't attack unless defending player controls an Island.\n{U}, Sacrifice an Island: Target land becomes an Island until end of turn.

name: Escape Artist
text: Escape Artist can't be blocked.\n{U}, Discard a card: Return Escape Artist to its owner's hand.
flavor: "Not even my shadow knows where I am."

name: Extract
text: Search target player's library for a card and exile it. Then that player shuffles his or her library.
flavor: To say Nixar had a splitting headache would be a bit of an understatement.

name: Fervent Denial
text: Counter target spell.\nFlashback {5}{U}{U} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)
flavor: "Your tenacity is admirable. And futile."\n—Emperor Aboshan

name: Immobilizing Ink
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature doesn't untap during its controller's untap step.\nEnchanted creature has "{1}, Discard a card: Untap this creature."

name: Laquatus's Creativity
text: Target player draws cards equal to the number of cards in his or her hand, then discards that many cards.
flavor: One never knows when inspiration will bubble up.

name: Patron Wizard
text: Tap an untapped Wizard you control: Counter target spell unless its controller pays {1}.
flavor: "The best way to teach is by example."

name: Pedantic Learning
text: Whenever a land card is put into your graveyard from your library, you may pay {1}. If you do, draw a card.
flavor: Even the trivial can inspire.

name: Peek
text: Look at target player's hand.\nDraw a card.
flavor: Sometimes you have to read between the minds.

name: Persuasion
text: Enchant creature (Target a creature as you cast this. This card enters the battlefield attached to that creature.)\nYou control enchanted creature.
flavor: "Protocol demands that you bow down before me. I always stand on protocol."

name: Phantom Whelp
text: When Phantom Whelp attacks or blocks, return it to its owner's hand at end of combat. (Return it only if it's on the battlefield.)
flavor: It lurks in the mist, waiting for stragglers to fall behind. When the fog clears, nothing remains but footprints.

name: Predict
text: Name a card, then target player puts the top card of his or her library into his or her graveyard. If that card is the named card, you draw two cards. Otherwise, you draw a card.

name: Psionic Gift
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature has "{T}: This creature deals 1 damage to target creature or player."
flavor: For sale: Complete wizard's library. Rare scrolls, grimoires, and works of ancient spellcrafting! Slightly abridged.

name: Pulsating Illusion
text: Flying\nDiscard a card: Pulsating Illusion gets +4/+4 until end of turn. Activate this ability only once each turn.

name: Puppeteer
text: {U}, {T}: You may tap or untap target creature.
flavor: "Getting people to do what you want is merely a matter of telling them what they want to hear."

name: Repel
text: Put target creature on top of its owner's library.
flavor: "I have a hunch we'll be seeing that one again soon."\n—Ambassador Laquatus

name: Rites of Refusal
text: Discard any number of cards. Counter target spell unless its controller pays {3} for each card discarded this way.

name: Scrivener
text: When Scrivener enters the battlefield, you may return target instant card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: A good memory is no match for a good scribe.

name: Shifty Doppelganger
text: {3}{U}, Exile Shifty Doppelganger: You may put a creature card from your hand onto the battlefield. If you do, that creature gains haste until end of turn. At the beginning of the next end step, sacrifice that creature. If you do, return Shifty Doppelganger to the battlefield.

name: Standstill
text: When a player casts a spell, sacrifice Standstill. If you do, each of that player's opponents draws three cards.
flavor: "Take your time."

name: Syncopate
text: Counter target spell unless its controller pays {X}. If that spell is countered this way, exile it instead of putting it into its owner's graveyard.
flavor: "Memories can't simply be washed away. The mind must be scrubbed clean."\n—Ambassador Laquatus

name: Think Tank
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, look at the top card of your library. You may put that card into your graveyard.
flavor: Cephalids seek knowledge not to better themselves, but to best others.

name: Thought Devourer
text: Flying\nYour maximum hand size is reduced by four.
flavor: Thinking is hard.

name: Thought Eater
text: Flying\nYour maximum hand size is reduced by three.
flavor: The first memory it sucks out of its host is how to get rid of it.

name: Thought Nibbler
text: Flying\nYour maximum hand size is reduced by two.
flavor: Balshan wizards have long used them to gnaw away the memories they wish to forget.

name: Time Stretch
text: Target player takes two extra turns after this one.
flavor: There's lots of time like the present.

name: Touch of Invisibility
text: Target creature can't be blocked this turn.\nDraw a card.
flavor: Cephalids specialize in things unseen, be they politics, betrayal, or themselves.

name: Traumatize
text: Target player puts the top half of his or her library, rounded down, into his or her graveyard.
flavor: Dreads had half a mind to leave.

name: Treetop Sentinel
text: Flying, protection from green
flavor: Crian's patrols afford him plenty of opportunity to take potshots at the "dirtwalkers" far below.

name: Unifying Theory
text: Whenever a player casts a spell, that player may pay {2}. If the player does, he or she draws a card.
flavor: Scribbles of a lunatic and formulas of a genius are often indistinguishable.

name: Upheaval
text: Return all permanents to their owners' hands.
flavor: The calm comes after the storm.

name: Words of Wisdom
text: You draw two cards, then each other player draws a card.
flavor: Knowledge can't be kept in a bottle or sealed in a box. It yearns to be spread and shared.

name: Afflict
text: Target creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn.\nDraw a card.
flavor: When one of the Patriarch's champions displeased him, he would only shake his finger. That was enough.

name: Bloodcurdler
text: Flying\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, put the top card of your library into your graveyard.\nThreshold — As long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard, Bloodcurdler gets +1/+1 and has "At the beginning of your end step, exile two cards from your graveyard."

name: Braids, Cabal Minion
text: At the beginning of each player's upkeep, that player sacrifices an artifact, creature, or land.
flavor: "Home is where you can find a decent graveyard and strangers can disappear without awkward questions."

name: Buried Alive
text: Search your library for up to three creature cards and put them into your graveyard. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: The scrape of shovels and the tumble of cold dirt soon muffled their pleas.

name: Cabal Inquisitor
text: Threshold — {1}{B}, {T}, Exile two cards from your graveyard: Target player discards a card. Activate this ability only any time you could cast a sorcery, and only if seven or more cards are in your graveyard.

name: Cabal Patriarch
text: {2}{B}, Sacrifice a creature: Target creature gets -2/-2 until end of turn.\n{2}{B}, Exile a creature card from your graveyard: Target creature gets -2/-2 until end of turn.

name: Cabal Shrine
text: Whenever a player casts a spell, that player discards X cards, where X is the number of cards in all graveyards with the same name as that spell.

name: Caustic Tar
text: Enchant land\nEnchanted land has "{T}: Target player loses 3 life."
flavor: "Twisted magic, twisted fate,\nForce the land to ooze with hate."\n—Cabal chant

name: Childhood Horror
text: Flying\nThreshold — As long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard, Childhood Horror gets +2/+2 and can't block.

name: Coffin Purge
text: Exile target card from a graveyard.\nFlashback {B} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Crypt Creeper
text: Sacrifice Crypt Creeper: Exile target card from a graveyard.
flavor: To unearth its dinner, it inters itself.

name: Cursed Monstrosity
text: Flying\nWhenever Cursed Monstrosity becomes the target of a spell or ability, sacrifice it unless you discard a land card.
flavor: "Run away! It's an . . . um . . . run away!"\n—Nomad sentry

name: Decaying Soil
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, exile a card from your graveyard.\nThreshold — As long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard, Decaying Soil has "Whenever a nontoken creature is put into your graveyard from the battlefield, you may pay {1}. If you do, return that card to your hand."

name: Decompose
text: Exile up to three target cards from a single graveyard.
flavor: "Sheesh! How am I supposed to make a decent living around here?"\n—Cabal grave robber

name: Diabolic Tutor
text: Search your library for a card and put that card into your hand. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: The best ideas often come from the worst minds.

name: Dirty Wererat
text: {B}, Discard a card: Regenerate Dirty Wererat.\nThreshold — As long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard, Dirty Wererat gets +2/+2 and can't block.

name: Dusk Imp
text: Flying
flavor: It despises humans and squirrels and beasts and dwarves and cephalids . . . well, it despises just about everything.

name: Entomb
text: Search your library for a card and put that card into your graveyard. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: A grave is the safest place to store ill-gotten treasures.

name: Execute
text: Destroy target white creature. It can't be regenerated.\nDraw a card.
flavor: "Any fool who would die for honor is better off dead."\n—Cabal Patriarch

name: Face of Fear
text: {2}{B}, Discard a card: Face of Fear gains fear until end of turn. (It can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)
flavor: "It's only frightened five people to death. Not my best work."\n—Braids, dementia summoner

name: Famished Ghoul
text: {1}{B}, Sacrifice Famished Ghoul: Exile up to two target cards from a single graveyard.
flavor: Memories have distinct tastes. Its favorites are the sickly sweetness of lost love and the bitter smokiness of cruel murder.

name: Filthy Cur
text: Whenever Filthy Cur is dealt damage, you lose that much life.
flavor: Some things even fleas won't bite.

name: Fledgling Imp
text: {B}, Discard a card: Fledgling Imp gains flying until end of turn.
flavor: Imps aren't born knowing how to fly—just how to annoy.

name: Frightcrawler
text: Fear (This creature can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)\nThreshold — As long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard, Frightcrawler gets +2/+2 and can't block.

name: Ghastly Demise
text: Destroy target nonblack creature if its toughness is less than or equal to the number of cards in your graveyard.
flavor: "Anyone can snap her fingers and yank a soul. I prefer to kill creatively."\n—Braids, dementia summoner

name: Gravedigger
text: When Gravedigger enters the battlefield, you may return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: Oddly, no one questioned the Cabal's wisdom in hiring a zombie to work at the cemetery.

name: Gravestorm
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, target opponent may exile a card from his or her graveyard. If that player doesn't, you may draw a card.

name: Haunting Echoes
text: Exile all cards from target player's graveyard other than basic land cards. For each card exiled this way, search that player's library for all cards with the same name as that card and exile them. Then that player shuffles his or her library.

name: Hint of Insanity
text: Target player reveals his or her hand. That player discards all nonland cards with the same name as another card in his or her hand.
flavor: "Practice makes perfect, but obsession makes better."

name: Infected Vermin
text: {2}{B}: Infected Vermin deals 1 damage to each creature and each player.\nThreshold — {3}{B}: Infected Vermin deals 3 damage to each creature and each player. Activate this ability only if seven or more cards are in your graveyard.

name: Innocent Blood
text: Each player sacrifices a creature.
flavor: Zombies mourn for the living and celebrate those who will soon be given the gift of death.

name: Last Rites
text: Discard any number of cards. Target player reveals his or her hand, then you choose a nonland card from it for each card discarded this way. That player discards those cards.

name: Malevolent Awakening
text: {1}{B}{B}, Sacrifice a creature: Return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: The most popular pit fighters are brought back for encore performances.

name: Mind Burst
text: Target player discards X cards, where X is one plus the number of cards named Mind Burst in all graveyards.
flavor: As haunting as a zombie's curse.

name: Mindslicer
text: When Mindslicer dies, each player discards his or her hand.
flavor: It is the thing that goes bump in the night.

name: Morbid Hunger
text: Morbid Hunger deals 3 damage to target creature or player. You gain 3 life.\nFlashback {7}{B}{B} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Morgue Theft
text: Return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.\nFlashback {4}{B} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Mortivore
text: Mortivore's power and toughness are each equal to the number of creature cards in all graveyards.\n{B}: Regenerate Mortivore.

name: Nefarious Lich
text: If damage would be dealt to you, exile that many cards from your graveyard instead. If you can't, you lose the game.\nIf you would gain life, draw that many cards instead.\nWhen Nefarious Lich leaves the battlefield, you lose the game.

name: Overeager Apprentice
text: Discard a card, Sacrifice Overeager Apprentice: Add {B}{B}{B} to your mana pool.
flavor: Slow and steady may not always win the race, but at least it doesn't end up splattered on the walls.

name: Painbringer
text: {T}, Exile any number of cards from your graveyard: Target creature gets -X/-X until end of turn, where X is the number of cards exiled this way.

name: Patriarch's Desire
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +2/-2.\nThreshold — Enchanted creature gets an additional +2/-2 as long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard.

name: Repentant Vampire
text: Flying\nWhenever a creature dealt damage by Repentant Vampire this turn dies, put a +1/+1 counter on Repentant Vampire.\nThreshold — As long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard, Repentant Vampire is white and has "{T}: Destroy target black creature."

name: Rotting Giant
text: Whenever Rotting Giant attacks or blocks, sacrifice it unless you exile a card from your graveyard.
flavor: Wracked with rot, it wrecks and ruins.

name: Sadistic Hypnotist
text: Sacrifice a creature: Target player discards two cards. Activate this ability only any time you could cast a sorcery.
flavor: "Victory in the pits is almost as rewarding as the methods I use to achieve it."

name: Screams of the Damned
text: {1}{B}, Exile a card from your graveyard: Screams of the Damned deals 1 damage to each creature and each player.
flavor: It's important to face your inner demons . . . unless they're the kind of demons that can kill you.

name: Skeletal Scrying
text: As an additional cost to cast Skeletal Scrying, exile X cards from your graveyard.\nYou draw X cards and you lose X life.

name: Skull Fracture
text: Target player discards a card.\nFlashback {3}{B} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Stalking Bloodsucker
text: Flying\n{1}{B}, Discard a card: Stalking Bloodsucker gets +2/+2 until end of turn.
flavor: The pits feed both its thirst for combat and its thirst for blood.

name: Tainted Pact
text: Exile the top card of your library. You may put that card into your hand unless it has the same name as another card exiled this way. Repeat this process until you put a card into your hand or you exile two cards with the same name, whichever comes first.

name: Tombfire
text: Target player exiles all cards with flashback from his or her graveyard.
flavor: The fondest memories burn brightest. As they're lost forever, the flames grow hotter still.

name: Traveling Plague
text:
Enchant creature
At the beginning of each upkeep, put a plague counter on Traveling Plague.
Enchanted creature gets -1/-1 for each plague counter on Traveling Plague.
When enchanted creature leaves the battlefield, that creature's controller returns Traveling Plague from its owner's graveyard to the battlefield.

name: Whispering Shade
text: Swampwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Swamp.)\n{B}: Whispering Shade gets +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: It glides through the shadows until it reaches yours.

name: Zombie Assassin
text: {T}, Exile two cards from your graveyard and Zombie Assassin: Destroy target nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated.
flavor: "Zombies don't kill. They recruit."\n—Braids, dementia summoner

name: Zombie Cannibal
text: Whenever Zombie Cannibal deals combat damage to a player, you may exile target card from that player's graveyard.
flavor: Nothing is sacred to the undead—not even their own kind.

name: Zombie Infestation
text: Discard two cards: Put a 2/2 black Zombie creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: The nomads' funeral pyres are more practical than ceremonial.

name: Zombify
text: Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
flavor: "The first birth celebrates life. The second birth mocks it."\n—Mystic elder

name: Acceptable Losses
text: As an additional cost to cast Acceptable Losses, discard a card at random.\nAcceptable Losses deals 5 damage to target creature.

name: Anarchist
text: When Anarchist enters the battlefield, you may return target sorcery card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: Those who will not follow are doomed to lead.

name: Ashen Firebeast
text: {1}{R}: Ashen Firebeast deals 1 damage to each creature without flying.
flavor: "I'm not sure which impresses me most, its thoroughness or its intensity."\n—Matoc, lavamancer

name: Barbarian Lunatic
text: {2}{R}, Sacrifice Barbarian Lunatic: Barbarian Lunatic deals 2 damage to target creature.
flavor: "I once saw a single barbarian charge a band of twenty nomads. I've seen some crazy ones, too."\n—Nomad sentry

name: Bash to Bits
text: Destroy target artifact.\nFlashback {4}{R}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Battle Strain
text: Whenever a creature blocks, Battle Strain deals 1 damage to that creature's controller.
flavor: The pits swallow the weak as predators swallow prey.

name: Blazing Salvo
text: Blazing Salvo deals 3 damage to target creature unless that creature's controller has Blazing Salvo deal 5 damage to him or her.
flavor: Barbarians equate courage with the ability to endure pain.

name: Bomb Squad
text: {T}: Put a fuse counter on target creature.\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, put a fuse counter on each creature with a fuse counter on it.\nWhenever a creature has four or more fuse counters on it, remove all fuse counters from it and destroy it. That creature deals 4 damage to its controller.

name: Burning Sands
text: Whenever a creature dies, that creature's controller sacrifices a land.
flavor: "Pain teaches lessons no scholar can."\n—Kamahl, pit fighter

name: Chainflinger
text: {1}{R}, {T}: Chainflinger deals 1 damage to target creature or player.\nThreshold — {2}{R}, {T}: Chainflinger deals 2 damage to target creature or player. Activate this ability only if seven or more cards are in your graveyard.

name: Chance Encounter
text: Whenever you win a coin flip, put a luck counter on Chance Encounter.\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, if Chance Encounter has ten or more luck counters on it, you win the game.
flavor: The more unlikely the victory, the more memorable the success.

name: Demolish
text: Destroy target artifact or land.
flavor: "Pound the steel until it fits.\nDoesn't work? Bash to bits."\n—Dwarven forging song

name: Demoralize
text: All creatures gain menace until end of turn. (They can't be blocked except by two or more creatures.)\nThreshold — If seven or more cards are in your graveyard, creatures can't block this turn.

name: Dwarven Grunt
text: Mountainwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Mountain.)
flavor: Hard as stone and twice as stubborn.\n—Dwarven compliment

name: Dwarven Recruiter
text: When Dwarven Recruiter enters the battlefield, search your library for any number of Dwarf cards and reveal those cards. Shuffle your library, then put them on top of it in any order.

name: Dwarven Shrine
text: Whenever a player casts a spell, Dwarven Shrine deals X damage to that player, where X is twice the number of cards in all graveyards with the same name as that spell.

name: Dwarven Strike Force
text: Discard a card at random: Dwarven Strike Force gains first strike and haste until end of turn.
flavor: Any given foothill may hide dozens of dwarves waiting to spill from their tunnels like fire ants.

name: Earth Rift
text: Destroy target land.\nFlashback {5}{R}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Ember Beast
text: Ember Beast can't attack or block alone.
flavor: Spot one ember beast, attack.\nSpot a second, best fall back.\n—Dwarven saying

name: Engulfing Flames
text: Engulfing Flames deals 1 damage to target creature. It can't be regenerated this turn.\nFlashback {3}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Epicenter
text: Target player sacrifices a land.\nThreshold — Each player sacrifices all lands he or she controls instead if seven or more cards are in your graveyard.
flavor: Sometimes destruction is Dominaria's way of rebuilding. Sometimes it's not.

name: Firebolt
text: Firebolt deals 2 damage to target creature or player.\nFlashback {4}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)
flavor: Reach out and torch someone.

name: Flame Burst
text: Flame Burst deals X damage to target creature or player, where X is 2 plus the number of cards named Flame Burst in all graveyards.
flavor: As hot as a dwarf's rage.

name: Frenetic Ogre
text: {R}, Discard a card at random: Frenetic Ogre gets +3/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: The best thing about ogres is that they never try to sneak up on you.

name: Halberdier
text: First strike
flavor: His reputation precedes him—and so does his weapon.

name: Impulsive Maneuvers
text: Whenever a creature attacks, flip a coin. If you win the flip, the next time that creature would deal combat damage this turn, it deals double that damage instead. If you lose the flip, the next time that creature would deal combat damage this turn, prevent that damage.

name: Kamahl, Pit Fighter
text: Haste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)\n{T}: Kamahl, Pit Fighter deals 3 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "I didn't come to play. I came to win."

name: Kamahl's Desire
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature has first strike.\nThreshold — Enchanted creature gets +3/+0 as long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard.

name: Lava Blister
text: Destroy target nonbasic land unless its controller has Lava Blister deal 6 damage to him or her.
flavor: To treat flesh wounds, use earth. To treat earth wounds, use flesh.\n—Barbarian saying

name: Liquid Fire
text: As an additional cost to cast Liquid Fire, choose a number between 0 and 5.\nLiquid Fire deals X damage to target creature and 5 minus X damage to that creature's controller, where X is the chosen number.
flavor: There's no such thing as a little bit of lava.

name: Mad Dog
text: At the beginning of your end step, if Mad Dog didn't attack or come under your control this turn, sacrifice it.
flavor: The bones it buries may be yours.

name: Magma Vein
text: {R}, Sacrifice a land: Magma Vein deals 1 damage to each creature without flying.
flavor: Standing near a volcano\n—Barbarian expression meaning\n"asking for it"

name: Magnivore
text: Haste (This creature can attack the turn it comes under your control.)\nMagnivore's power and toughness are each equal to the number of sorcery cards in all graveyards.

name: Mine Layer
text: {1}{R}, {T}: Put a mine counter on target land.\nWhenever a land with a mine counter on it becomes tapped, destroy it.\nWhen Mine Layer leaves the battlefield, remove all mine counters from all lands.

name: Minotaur Explorer
text: When Minotaur Explorer enters the battlefield, sacrifice it unless you discard a card at random.
flavor: After the invasion devastated the Talruum and Hurloon tribes, the survivors began to search for other minotaurs.

name: Molten Influence
text: Counter target instant or sorcery spell unless its controller has Molten Influence deal 4 damage to him or her.
flavor: Lavamancers make simple requests: obey or die.

name: Mudhole
text: Target player exiles all land cards from his or her graveyard.
flavor: "Doing okay back there, Tarv? Tarv?"

name: Need for Speed
text: Sacrifice a land: Target creature gains haste until end of turn.
flavor: His feet buckled the ground, his hands cut the wind to ribbons, and he was gone.

name: Obstinate Familiar
text: If you would draw a card, you may skip that draw instead.
flavor: "Lizards make excellent familiars. They never know when they've lost."\n—Matoc, lavamancer

name: Pardic Firecat
text: Haste\nIf Pardic Firecat is in a graveyard, effects from spells named Flame Burst count it as a card named Flame Burst.
flavor: "I've heard of putting the cat out, but this isn't what I had in mind."\n—Nomad sentry

name: Pardic Miner
text: Sacrifice Pardic Miner: Target player can't play lands this turn.
flavor:
"Punch and drag,
Toss the slag,
Sift the soil,
Leave the spoil."

name: Pardic Swordsmith
text: {R}, Discard a card at random: Pardic Swordsmith gets +2/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: A finely crafted blade will never meet as many blows on the battlefield as it did on the anvil.

name: Price of Glory
text: Whenever a player taps a land for mana, if it's not that player's turn, destroy that land.
flavor: "True strength lies in action. Let the weak react to me."\n—Kamahl, pit fighter

name: Reckless Charge
text: Target creature gets +3/+0 and gains haste until end of turn.\nFlashback {2}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Recoup
text: Target sorcery card in your graveyard gains flashback until end of turn. The flashback cost is equal to its mana cost. (Mana cost includes color.)\nFlashback {3}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Rites of Initiation
text: Discard any number of cards at random. Creatures you control get +1/+0 until end of turn for each card discarded this way.

name: Savage Firecat
text: Trample\nSavage Firecat enters the battlefield with seven +1/+1 counters on it.\nWhenever you tap a land for mana, remove a +1/+1 counter from Savage Firecat.

name: Scorching Missile
text: Scorching Missile deals 4 damage to target player.\nFlashback {9}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Seize the Day
text: Untap target creature. After this main phase, there is an additional combat phase followed by an additional main phase.\nFlashback {2}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Shower of Coals
text: Shower of Coals deals 2 damage to each of up to three target creatures and/or players.\nThreshold — Shower of Coals deals 4 damage to each of those creatures and/or players instead if seven or more cards are in your graveyard.

name: Spark Mage
text: Whenever Spark Mage deals combat damage to a player, you may have Spark Mage deal 1 damage to target creature that player controls.
flavor: The Pardic Mountains are known for their spicy cuisine.

name: Steam Vines
text: Enchant land\nWhen enchanted land becomes tapped, destroy it and Steam Vines deals 1 damage to that land's controller. That player attaches Steam Vines to a land of his or her choice.

name: Thermal Blast
text: Thermal Blast deals 3 damage to target creature.\nThreshold — Thermal Blast deals 5 damage to that creature instead if seven or more cards are in your graveyard.

name: Tremble
text: Each player sacrifices a land.
flavor: Otaria's frequent tremors are the last stages of Dominaria's recovery from the Phyrexian war.

name: Volcanic Spray
text: Volcanic Spray deals 1 damage to each creature without flying and each player.\nFlashback {1}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Volley of Boulders
text: Volley of Boulders deals 6 damage divided as you choose among any number of target creatures and/or players.\nFlashback {R}{R}{R}{R}{R}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Whipkeeper
text: {T}: Whipkeeper deals damage to target creature equal to the damage already dealt to it this turn.
flavor: "If you don't hit your adversaries while they're down, they might get up again."

name: Bearscape
text: {1}{G}, Exile two cards from your graveyard: Put a 2/2 green Bear creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: "Nature is the endless dance between life and death."\n—Seton, centaur druid

name: Beast Attack
text: Put a 4/4 green Beast creature token onto the battlefield.\nFlashback {2}{G}{G}{G} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Call of the Herd
text: Put a 3/3 green Elephant creature token onto the battlefield.\nFlashback {3}{G} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Cartographer
text: When Cartographer enters the battlefield, you may return target land card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: "Finding the way once is luck. Finding the way twice takes a good map."

name: Chatter of the Squirrel
text: Put a 1/1 green Squirrel creature token onto the battlefield.\nFlashback {1}{G} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Chlorophant
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, you may put a +1/+1 counter on Chlorophant.\nThreshold — As long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard, Chlorophant has "At the beginning of your upkeep, you may put another +1/+1 counter on Chlorophant."

name: Crashing Centaur
text: {G}, Discard a card: Crashing Centaur gains trample until end of turn.\nThreshold — As long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard, Crashing Centaur gets +2/+2 and has shroud. (It can't be the target of spells or abilities.)

name: Deep Reconnaissance
text: Search your library for a basic land card and put that card onto the battlefield tapped. Then shuffle your library.\nFlashback {4}{G} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Diligent Farmhand
text: {1}{G}, Sacrifice Diligent Farmhand: Search your library for a basic land card and put that card onto the battlefield tapped. Then shuffle your library.\nIf Diligent Farmhand is in a graveyard, effects from spells named Muscle Burst count it as a card named Muscle Burst.

name: Druid Lyrist
text: {G}, {T}, Sacrifice Druid Lyrist: Destroy target enchantment.
flavor: The druids and the forest are in perfect harmony. They sing the same songs.

name: Druid's Call
text: Enchant creature\nWhenever enchanted creature is dealt damage, its controller puts that many 1/1 green Squirrel creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: Suffer the little creatures, for they may yet rise up and beat you senseless.

name: Elephant Ambush
text: Put a 3/3 green Elephant creature token onto the battlefield.\nFlashback {6}{G}{G} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Gorilla Titan
text: Trample\nGorilla Titan gets +4/+4 as long as there are no cards in your graveyard.
flavor: "I want a banana this big!"

name: Ground Seal
text: When Ground Seal enters the battlefield, draw a card.\nCards in graveyards can't be the targets of spells or abilities.
flavor: "Let all we have buried be buried forever."\n—Seton, centaur druid

name: Holistic Wisdom
text: {2}, Exile a card from your hand: Return target card from your graveyard to your hand if it shares a card type with the card exiled this way. (Artifact, creature, enchantment, instant, land, planeswalker, sorcery, and tribal are card types.)

name: Howling Gale
text: Howling Gale deals 1 damage to each creature with flying and each player.\nFlashback {1}{G} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Ivy Elemental
text: Ivy Elemental enters the battlefield with X +1/+1 counters on it.
flavor: In the gardens of the centaurs, many travelers have mysteriously vanished while admiring the elaborate topiaries.

name: Krosan Archer
text: Reach (This creature can block creatures with flying.)\n{G}, Discard a card: Krosan Archer gets +0/+2 until end of turn.

name: Krosan Avenger
text: Trample\nThreshold — {1}{G}: Regenerate Krosan Avenger. Activate this ability only if seven or more cards are in your graveyard.
flavor: She'd have a fearsome reputation if she left any survivors.

name: Krosan Beast
text: Threshold — Krosan Beast gets +7/+7 as long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard.
flavor: Those who see the squirrels go underground in the winter aren't ready for what emerges in the spring.

name: Leaf Dancer
text: Forestwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Forest.)
flavor: A leaf dancer sweeps through the forest like a spring breeze, evading even the sharpest eyes and ears.

name: Metamorphic Wurm
text: Threshold — Metamorphic Wurm gets +4/+4 as long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard.
flavor: Only a handful have seen it transform. Or, from the wurm's perspective, only a mouthful.

name: Moment's Peace
text: Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt this turn.\nFlashback {2}{G} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Muscle Burst
text: Target creature gets +X/+X until end of turn, where X is 3 plus the number of cards named Muscle Burst in all graveyards.
flavor: As strong as a centaur's will.

name: Nantuko Disciple
text: {G}, {T}: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn.
flavor: Unanswered prayers are themselves answers.\n—Nantuko teaching

name: Nantuko Elder
text: {T}: Add {C}{G} to your mana pool.
flavor: Plant a field with wishes, and you will grow more wishes.\n—Nantuko teaching

name: Nantuko Mentor
text: {2}{G}, {T}: Target creature gets +X/+X until end of turn, where X is that creature's power.
flavor: That which grows without roots cannot be uprooted.\n—Nantuko teaching

name: Nantuko Shrine
text: Whenever a player casts a spell, that player puts X 1/1 green Squirrel creature tokens onto the battlefield, where X is the number of cards in all graveyards with the same name as that spell.

name: New Frontiers
text: Each player may search his or her library for up to X basic land cards and put them onto the battlefield tapped. Then each player who searched his or her library this way shuffles it.
flavor: Spreading a blanket of growth to warm a weary world.

name: Nimble Mongoose
text: Shroud (This creature can't be the target of spells or abilities.)\nThreshold — Nimble Mongoose gets +2/+2 as long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard.
flavor: Faster than a cobra's bite.

name: Nut Collector
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, you may put a 1/1 green Squirrel creature token onto the battlefield.\nThreshold — Squirrel creatures get +2/+2 as long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard.

name: Overrun
text: Creatures you control get +3/+3 and gain trample until end of turn.
flavor: The dance of angry feet\n—Nantuko expression meaning\n"stampede"

name: Piper's Melody
text: Shuffle any number of target creature cards from your graveyard into your library.
flavor: Those who follow nature's path eventually walk in a circle.

name: Primal Frenzy
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature has trample.
flavor: "Don't dismiss its anger as mindless fury. I assure you, it has purpose."\n—Seton, centaur druid

name: Rabid Elephant
text: Whenever Rabid Elephant becomes blocked, it gets +2/+2 until end of turn for each creature blocking it.
flavor: When in doubt, stomp.

name: Refresh
text: Regenerate target creature.\nDraw a card.
flavor: Death is a moth that dances toward our inner flame. The brightest fire can singe its wings.\n—Nantuko teaching

name: Rites of Spring
text: Discard any number of cards. Search your library for up to that many basic land cards, reveal those cards, and put them into your hand. Then shuffle your library.

name: Roar of the Wurm
text: Put a 6/6 green Wurm creature token onto the battlefield.\nFlashback {3}{G} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Seton, Krosan Protector
text: Tap an untapped Druid you control: Add {G} to your mana pool.
flavor: "Survival of the fittest is not only the law of the pits, it is the law of nature. That is why I fight."

name: Seton's Desire
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +2/+2.\nThreshold — As long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard, all creatures able to block enchanted creature do so.

name: Simplify
text: Each player sacrifices an enchantment.
flavor: A blossom's petals close inward to shut out the frost.\n—Nantuko teaching

name: Skyshooter
text: Reach (This creature can block creatures with flying.)\n{T}, Sacrifice Skyshooter: Destroy target attacking or blocking creature with flying.

name: Spellbane Centaur
text: Creatures you control can't be the targets of blue spells or abilities from blue sources.
flavor: "No mage's deception can harm those who keep nature balanced."

name: Springing Tiger
text: Threshold — Springing Tiger gets +2/+2 as long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard.
flavor: The ground trembled in a violent purr.

name: Squirrel Mob
text: Squirrel Mob gets +1/+1 for each other Squirrel on the battlefield.
flavor: An army of squirrels is still an army.

name: Squirrel Nest
text: Enchant land\nEnchanted land has "{T}: Put a 1/1 green Squirrel creature token onto the battlefield."
flavor: In the Krosan Forest, you've got to keep an eye out for the squirrels.

name: Still Life
text: {G}{G}: Still Life becomes a 4/3 Centaur creature in addition to its other types until end of turn.
flavor: The centaurs' simple magic can undo a basilisk's gaze, but only for a short time.

name: Stone-Tongue Basilisk
text: Whenever Stone-Tongue Basilisk deals combat damage to a creature, destroy that creature at end of combat.\nThreshold — As long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard, all creatures able to block Stone-Tongue Basilisk do so.

name: Sylvan Might
text: Target creature gets +2/+2 and gains trample until end of turn.\nFlashback {2}{G}{G} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Terravore
text: Trample\nTerravore's power and toughness are each equal to the number of land cards in all graveyards.

name: Twigwalker
text: {1}{G}, Sacrifice Twigwalker: Two target creatures each get +2/+2 until end of turn.
flavor: "Break one in half and you'll get a decent—if gooey—pair of weapons."\n—Centaur warrior

name: Verdant Succession
text: Whenever a green nontoken creature dies, that creature's controller may search his or her library for a card with the same name as that creature and put it onto the battlefield. If that player does, he or she shuffles his or her library.

name: Vivify
text: Target land becomes a 3/3 creature until end of turn. It's still a land.\nDraw a card.
flavor: Near the Krosan border, farmers keep watch over their fields lest the sod get up and wander away.

name: Werebear
text: {T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.\nThreshold — Werebear gets +3/+3 as long as seven or more cards are in your graveyard.
flavor: He exercises his right to bear arms.

name: Wild Mongrel
text: Discard a card: Wild Mongrel gets +1/+1 and becomes the color of your choice until end of turn.
flavor: It teaches you to play dead.

name: Woodland Druid
flavor:
What is a tree?
Slow hard thought.
What is a flower?
Swift soft flesh.
What is a druid?
Both.

name: Zoologist
text: {3}{G}, {T}: Reveal the top card of your library. If it's a creature card, put it onto the battlefield. Otherwise, put it into your graveyard.
flavor: "With friends like these, who needs people?"

name: Atogatog
text: Sacrifice an Atog creature: Atogatog gets +X/+X until end of turn, where X is the sacrificed creature's power.
flavor: It relishes old-fashioned family meals.

name: Decimate
text: Destroy target artifact, target creature, target enchantment, and target land.
flavor: "Anyone can admire creation. Only a barbarian sees the beauty in demolition."\n—Kamahl, pit fighter

name: Iridescent Angel
